result.formatted_address: Baskerville House, 22 Ice House St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Sushi Sase

reviews.text: Sase used to be my favourite in HK before they moved, and even better if you're lucky enough to book Chef Sase himself. Well, went back for dinner after the move - food was still good but somehow lacked the sparkle that I used to love. Price is still steep.
Food was great, especially the Tako. Hygiene was exceptional as well, do keep in mind to make reservation as seats are very limited. Fresh seafood at its best, and definitely some amazing knifework.

Ordered the Sakura 15 pc sushi omakase for dinner. Quality and service both met expectations. The chef kept it pretty low risk and simple for the most part but used just enough twists at times (e.g. use of lime, herbs, spices) to elevate the flavor. Its hard to go wrong here, although if you are a sushi connoisseur looking for something more original and different, you might want to explore other places.

It is a very good option. I thought the sushi had a little too much seasoning but for the pieces that were pure like the uni I thought they were excellent and very fresh. Price is fully valued but not unfair.
Great Japanese food but abit over priced.
